title: Six die after 'attack by killer bees' following bus crash
description: Six people including an eight-year-old girl have died after they were reportedly attacked by killer bees when the bus they were travelling in crashed in Nicaragua.

title: News is under assault because readers 'not open to best obtainable version of truth'
description: Fact-based news is under assault in this world increasingly famished for enquiry, according to a summit on investigative journalism held in London.

title: There's plenty of scope to misjudge - Imran Khan's arrest could play into his hands but it could also inspire violence
description: This could be a defining moment for Pakistan.

title: Former Russian state TV journalist claims Putin 'doesn't have enough Novichok' to kill critics
description: A former Russian state TV journalist has claimed that an "isolated" Vladimir Putin "doesn't have enough Novichok" to kill his growing number of critics.

title: Finland prime minister Sanna Marin to divorce husband of three years
description: Finland's outgoing prime minister Sanna Marin has announced she and her husband of three years, Markus Raikkonen, are divorcing.

title: Josef Fritzl 'sure' he will be 'reunited' with his family
description: Sex offender Josef Fritzl has claimed in an interview he thinks his family will "forgive" him for his crimes and believes he will be "reunited" with them.

title: With great power comes great responsibility: The Pope 'meets Spider-Man' in the Vatican City
description: The Pope would have felt the Vatican was in safe hands on Wednesday when the friendly neighbourhood Spider-Man swung by after the pontiff's weekly audience.

title: More than 200 rockets fired from Gaza after Israeli air strikes
description: Around 270 rockets were fired from Gaza towards Israel early on Wednesday afternoon.

title: Imran Khan set for major showdown with Pakistan's ruling elites - and UK has reasons to be worried
description: We are used to seeing political infighting in Pakistan but the fate of Imran Khan and ensuing unrest is raising major concerns across the region and as far afield as the UK.

title: Six dead after police officer shoots colleague before attacking Tunisian synagogue
description: Six people have died in Tunisia after a police officer shot a colleague and opened fire on a 2,500-year-old synagogue.

title: Man dies and wife fights for life after suspected gas leak at holiday villa
description: An Edinburgh man has died and his wife is fighting for her life after a suspected carbon monoxide leak at a holiday home in Spain.

title: Nearly 1,000 of Imran Khan's supporters detained - ahead of march to protest against his arrest
description: Supporters of Imran Khan, the former prime minister of Pakistan, are planning a protest march to Islamabad today where he is being held in custody on corruption charges - after almost 1,000 of them were arrested in one province alone.

title: Several dead during violent protests as Imran Khan to be held for eight days
description: At least four people have died and hundreds have been detained during violent protests in Pakistan over the arrest of Imran Khan - the country's former prime minister -  who has been remanded in custody for eight days.

title: Police believe 22 women were murdered and need help to name them
description: Police in Belgium, Germany and the Netherlands are asking for the public's help to identify 22 women and girls who they believe have been murdered.
